				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13111446/scp-5560#post-4838819</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 07 Dec 2020 13:53:51 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Gaffsey</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>6590029</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>There are a lot of questions I have about why Anderson chose to make &quot;more like humans&quot; the benchmark for artificial intelligence. I seems like someone with that tenuous a grip on reality and that level of skill would look to &quot;exceed&quot; human capacities in some meaningful way that might make it more alien to us than &quot;normal person, but they can predict the future.&quot; This reminded me a lot of the Little Misters series, more than anything. Not a complaint, as I like the Little Misters, but yeah, I got some old school vibes from this.</p> <p>The ending was quite sweet, though. +1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
